<p><i><b>The Boston Globe</b></i> (and the <i><b>Boston Sunday Globe</b></i>) is an <a href="United_States" title="United States">American</a> daily <a href="Newspaper" title="Newspaper">newspaper</a> based in <a href="Boston" title="Boston">Boston</a>, <a href="Massachusetts" title="Massachusetts">Massachusetts</a>. <i>The Boston Globe</i> has been owned by <a href="The_New_York_Times_Company" title="The New York Times Company">The New York Times Company</a> since 1993. Its chief print rival is the <i><a href="Boston_Herald" title="Boston Herald">Boston Herald</a></i>.<sup id="cite_ref-3" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-3"><span>[</span>3<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
<p><i>The Boston Globe</i> has won 21 <a href="Pulitzer_Prize" title="Pulitzer Prize">Pulitzer Prizes</a>.</p>
